public interface ReportBuilder
extends AggregateBuilder

A "fluent" interface that is used in Aggregator to provide declarative ordering and filtering.

filtered

ReportBuilder filtered(Filter filter)
Declares that this ReporterBuilder is constrained to records allowed by the specified filter. The report(gr.forth.ics.jbenchy.Aggregate, Object[]) and deleteRecords() methods will only apply to these records.

Note that subsequent calls to this method further constrain this ReporterBuilder; they do not replace existing filters. For a record to be reported, it is needed that it is allowed by all defined filters, i.e. with conjunction ("and") semantics.

Returns:
this
See Also:
report(gr.forth.ics.jbenchy.Aggregate, Object[]), deleteRecords(), Filters

deleteRecords

void deleteRecords()
Deletes all records which are not filtered out. For example, to delete all records having COLOR=="RED", this idiom would probably be used:
aggregator.filtered(Filters.eq("COLOR", "RED")).deleteRecords();

See Also:
filtered(Filter)
